From 94686b2417c75942cff13e5b74b4ea9cf6bfdbf7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Iulian Mocanu <iulian.mocanu@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 13:17:02 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix bnxt_en and bnxt_re build against Linux 6.16+ and 6.18+

This patch adds kernel-version preprocessor guards to accommodate
upstream API changes that break the out-of-tree Broadcom bnxt drivers:

Kernel 6.16:
 - devlink_health_reporter_create() dropped the graceful_period argument.
 - cyclecounter_read_t now takes a const pointer.

Kernel 6.18:
 - UDP_TUNNEL_NIC_INFO_MAY_SLEEP flag removed.
 - ethtool get_fec_stats() gained a struct ethtool_fec_hist * parameter.
 - __inet6_lookup_established() / inet_lookup_established() dropped hashinfo.
 - xdp_update_skb_shared_info() renamed to xdp_update_skb_frags_info().
 - ib_device_ops reg_user_mr / reg_user_mr_dmabuf gained struct ib_dmah *.

Also fixes a Makefile issue where KDIR is unset when LINUX is provided,
and adds -I$(KDIR)/include to the bnxt_re OFED include paths.

Signed-off-by: Iulian Mocanu <iulian.mocanu@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Catalin Rapiteanu <viorel-catalin.rapiteanu@windriver.com>
---
